docs/DOCUMENTATION_COVERAGE.yaml:188:          - git restore .agentic/workflow_state docs/reports/CURRENT_WORKFLOW_OUTPUT.md
docs/STATUS.md:247:- Workflow rule added: larger terminal runs should write committed logs under `docs/reports/terminal/`, allowing `d` to mean seen-and-continue after PASS without pasting terminal output.
docs/STATUS.md:272:PR #375 added the terminal log finalization guard. Long terminal runs should tee into a temporary log outside `docs/reports/terminal/`, then finalize the completed log with `./ns terminal-finalize <tmp-log> <name>` before staging, committing, and pushing. Finalization rejects active repo-log sources and logs without an explicit PASS, FAIL, or PENDING result marker.
docs/workflow/WORK_ORDERS.md:45:The expected branch must be a non-main slice branch. The log path must be under `docs/reports/terminal/` and must be listed in `expected_outputs`.
docs/workflow/WORK_ORDER_TEMPLATES.md:17:- Logs must be written under `docs/reports/terminal/`.
docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:15:- Every larger workflow block must write its complete terminal output to `docs/reports/terminal/*.log`.
docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:37:- `./ns run-logged <name> -- <command...>`: runs a local command while teeing output into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log` and updates `LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt`.
docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:44:Commands executed through `./ns run-logged` must not use plain `test -z "$(git status --short)"` as a cleanliness gate, because `run-logged` necessarily updates `docs/reports/terminal/LATEST_TERMINAL_LOG.txt` and creates a terminal log.
docs/workflow/TERMINAL_LOG_HANDOFF_RULE.md:54:Do not commit a repository log file while the current process is still writing to it. Long scripts must tee into a temporary log outside `docs/reports/terminal/`, then finalize the completed log into `docs/reports/terminal/*.log` with `./ns terminal-finalize <tmp-log> <name>` before staging, committing, and pushing. The finalized log must contain an explicit `### RESULT: PASS ###`, `### RESULT: FAIL ###`, or `### RESULT: PENDING ###` marker.
